Brazilian Stock Movers: BM&FBovespa, Cyrela, Embraer, Gol Linhas

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-08-01T15:31:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/brazilian-stock-movers-bm-fbovespa-cyrela-embraer-gol-linhas.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:12 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.7 percent to 58,8410.38.  BM&FBovespa SA (BVMF3)  (BVMF3 BS), the operator of  Latin America ’s
biggest securities exchange, dropped 1.3 percent to 8.95 reais,
its sixth decline in seven trading sessions, after Finance
Minister  Guido Mantega  said  Brazil  may take additional steps to
curb currency gains.  Cyrela Brazil Realty SA Empreendimentos e Participacoes (CYRE3) 
(CYRE3 BS), Brazil’s second-biggest homebuilder by revenue, fell
3.1 percent to 14.73 as economists covering the Brazilian
economy increased their forecast for inflation in 2013 for the
first time.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS) dropped 1.6
percent to 11.81 reais as the Brazilian airline was lowered to
“neutral” from “buy” at UBS AG, which lowered its forecast
for the margin on earnings before interest and taxes, according
to an investor note today from analyst Victor Mizusaki.  To contact the reporter on this story:
